1
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:10,100
♪I love the clarity in your eyes♪

2
00:00:10,740 --> 00:00:13,860
♪Like a shooting star across my world♪

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,580
♪Repeating the goodbye we never said♪

4
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:21,540
♪Through sleepless nights♪

5
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,100
♪I miss the way you looked at me♪

6
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:30,260
♪Like photos freezing that summer bit by bit♪

7
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:35,380
♪By the shore with warm winds, maybe we'll meet again♪

8
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:41,460
[Fall in Love Again]

9
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:43,980
[Episode 6]

10
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:49,680
Hasn't Xi been through enough already?

11
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:53,000
A woman who wasted four whole years.

12
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:54,960
Her husband cheated.

13
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:57,160
Her career came to a halt.

14
00:00:57,440 --> 00:00:58,560
On top of that marriage

15
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,560
and the divorce.

16
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:05,510
This is your third time playing the hero, right?

17
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,040
You always show up at the perfect moment.

18
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:10,560
Why not use the chance and confess?

19
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:12,920
It's not like I didn't.

20
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:16,200
Which role made you start liking me?

21
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,400
I like every role you've played.

22
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,640
As an actor, you should know

23
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,920
every character an actor plays

24
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,360
is very different from who they really are.

25
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:35,960
I know.

26
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:38,880
All your characters

27
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,040
are nothing compared to you.

28
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:43,600
Not bad, Chu Jingxi.

29
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,800
Still as charming as ever.

30
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:46,560
Thanks,

31
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,160
for liking me.

32
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:55,120
That's it?

33
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:56,720
Yeah.

34
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,360
Thanks for liking me.

35
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:01,160
I don't want "thanks for liking me".

36
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:03,880
I want "you love me" or "I love you"!

37
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,560
Come on, stop it.

38
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,720
That's exactly what she said to me.

39
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:13,440
I'm telling you.

40
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,280
From my experience,

41
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:16,560
the two of you,

42
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:17,520
there's something there.

43
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:18,720
Really.

44
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:19,960
Absolutely.

45
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,960
Go on.

46
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,680
Stop teasing, love guru.

47
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:31,000
When a woman's heartbroken

48
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,160
and work isn't going well.

49
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,520
If she can tell you all this,

50
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:36,160
she definitely likes you.

51
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,160
I'm telling you.

52
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,560
Even tough women soften with persistence.

53
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,240
You've got to make the first move, hear me?

54
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:46,360
Go for it!

55
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,600
You're getting it.

56
00:02:57,560 --> 00:03:00,000
I've got another way to heal a broken heart.

57
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,040
The time-heals-all method.

58
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:04,080
Keep yourself fully busy,

59
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:05,600
then you won't have time to be sad.

60
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,760
I've been busy nonstop lately,

61
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,160
but it hasn't worked at all.

62
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,200
Then do you want to stay busy with me?

63
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:15,840
How about this? Let's start a company.

64
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,320
You're serious?

65
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,360
Dead serious.

66
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,120
Look.

67
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:24,480
I've built up tons of connections and resources.

68
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,720
And you've been out of the spotlight for years,

69
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,960
yet you ran Qi Siqin's company so well.

70
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,840
And even as an actress,

71
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,120
you still have market value.

72
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,400
I didn't tell you,

73
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,640
I've wanted to quit for a long time.

74
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,440
Are you okay?

75
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:38,120
I'm already in my thirties.

76
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,480
My prime years as an actress are gone.

77
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,520
It's never too late for good things.

78
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,760
Where did that comeback fire go?

79
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:46,920
Don't get me started.

80
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,360
First burst of energy,

81
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,520
then it fades, then it's gone.

82
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:54,040
I'm your shot of adrenaline.

83
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:56,720
No.

84
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,960
I'll keep trying, but...

85
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,200
No buts.

86
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,960
Look at you right now.

87
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:05,160
You're stuck in a spiral of self-doubt.

88
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,800
Are you afraid you'll drag me down?

89
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,960
I'm still at rock bottom myself.

90
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:17,560
If we start a company together,

91
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,560
it'll be a losing deal.

92
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,160
I believe in you.

93
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,840
More importantly, I believe in myself.

94
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:25,960
Just one question.

95
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:26,840
Do you dare to do it?

96
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,280
Are you in or not?

97
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:32,320
I'm in.

98
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:33,880
Louder.

99
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:34,840
Do you dare?

100
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:35,280
I'm in!

101
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,920
Do you dare?

102
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:37,760
I'm in!

103
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,160
Who is it?

104
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:42,960
No idea.

105
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,760
I'll go check.

106
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,800
He Zheng?

107
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,160
Yang.

108
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,280
What's going on?

109
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,720
I don't know.

110
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:00,000
Why are you yelling along?

111
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,640
I heard what you were saying.

112
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:03,680
It was pretty hype,

113
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,720
so I couldn't help shouting too.

114
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,560
What are you doing here?

115
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,320
You're...?

116
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:12,680
Just passing by.

117
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,360
Passing by?

118
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,960
Want to pass by inside too?

119
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:18,360
Sure.

120
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:19,200
Wait.

121
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,640
I didn't...

122
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,640
Ms. Chu, I brought you some snacks.

123
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:25,680
And,

124
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,680
this one's for you too.

125
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:28,520
Thanks.

126
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:29,840
No problem.

127
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:33,360
What's going on?

128
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:34,600
Don't worry about it.

129
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:38,640
You two talk.

130
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,560
Really making yourself at home.

131
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,200
If we're starting a company,

132
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,360
the first step is choosing a location.

133
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,520
Any thoughts?

134
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:53,320
You should decide the location.

135
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:55,160
I saw a place before called

136
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,040
Fanmu Startup Park.

137
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,960
You'll like the environment and location.

138
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,440
I can take you to check it out.

139
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:01,880
You're starting a company?

140
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,040
Count me in.

141
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,320
I'll work for you.

142
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,600
Is your contract up?

143
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,440
If you terminate it,

144
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,600
can you afford the penalty?

145
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:14,160
I can handle the contract myself.

146
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:17,320
Breaking a contract hurts an actor badly,

147
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,720
and you're at a key growth stage.

148
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,560
Don't think you're young

149
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,840
and waste your youth.

150
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:23,640
I'm telling you.

151
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:26,080
A lot of things need careful thought.

152
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:27,840
Got it.

153
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:29,480
Thanks, Chu.

154
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,000
What did you call me?

155
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,000
How about Xi instead?

156
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:35,800
Stop right there.

157
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,640
If you don't want it too formal,

158
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,240
and don't want to call me Ms. Chu,

159
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,320
just call me Xi.

160
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:43,840
Okay.

161
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:45,760
Am I invisible to you two?

162
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,640
Young people can be impulsive,

163
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,000
but you've got good judgment.

164
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,560
If you join our company,

165
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,920
we'll definitely invest in you,

166
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,000
with a top agent like me backing you.

167
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,520
If your termination fee's an issue,

168
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,920
we can help cover part of it.

169
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,800
No need, I can handle it.

170
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:04,880
What are you doing?

171
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,000
The company's not even set up yet,

172
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,320
and you're already helping with his penalty?

173
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:07,920
What's wrong?

174
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:10,840
Look at him.

175
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:13,520
He's clearly a solid investment.

176
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,640
We need talent like him right now.

177
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,760
Who knows?

178
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:19,160
He might be our cash cow someday.

179
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:36,160
Congrats on the opening!

180
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:44,360
- Congrats on the opening! - Congrats!

181
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:47,680
- Great. - Great.

182
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,780
Here's to going big and strong?

183
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:58,120
[Origin]

184
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,680
We can plan another section here later.

185
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,360
How does that sound?

186
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:02,360
Hello, Ms. Chu.

187
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:02,960
Hello, Ms. Yang.

188
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,960
Are you happy with the new company, Ms. Chu?

189
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,280
You did a great job.

190
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,800
I'm very satisfied.

191
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,800
There's something you'll like even more.

192
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,400
[Have Fun]

193
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,120
Take a look.

194
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,560
Isn't this the IP we saw potential in?

195
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,440
If you want a breakout hit,

196
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:30,080
you have to do the project you value most.

197
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,150
Before, we could only watch from the sidelines.

198
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:36,150
Now we can finally do it ourselves.

199
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,120
Then let's seize this chance.

200
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,280
We have to.

201
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:47,600
♪You spread your wings♪

202
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,520
♪And met your destiny♪

203
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:54,600
♪How lucky he must be♪

204
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:56,600
Nice singing.

205
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,720
That was really good.

206
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,480
Director Qi.

207
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,240
They say beauty brings ruin.

208
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:05,760
Since you got Yu, you stopped filming.

209
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,400
So you've found true love?

210
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,280
You think Director Qi didn't want to work?

211
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:11,160
It's just that no one asked him.

212
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,160
If you can't hold your liquor,

213
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,000
then drink less.

214
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,320
How many have you had?

215
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:16,840
Qi.

216
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:17,480
You're talking nonsense.

217
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:21,800
Don't blame us for being blunt.

218
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:24,560
We're worried about you.

219
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:25,720
Your ex-wife.

220
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:28,600
Her company's booming.

221
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:32,080
I hear she's already hunting for projects.

222
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:34,840
She's running a company and sourcing projects?

223
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:36,400
Collecting IPs everywhere,

224
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,240
and paying good money.

225
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,160
A lot of companies

226
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,560
are sending scripts to her.

227
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,880
I heard though,

228
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:47,440
she's already set her sights on an EM IP.

229
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,040
EM's a major company.

230
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,560
Why would they pick a startup?

231
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,720
You never know.

232
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:54,880
I'll say it!

233
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,440
Her project will fail!

234
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,680
And her company won't last!

235
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:18,020
[Origin Planning Proposal]

236
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:21,020
[Have Fun Adaptation Materials]

237
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:29,080
Very good. You're well prepared.

238
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,880
And your future planning is solid.

239
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,360
But before anything is finalized,

240
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,160
it's all just talk.

241
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:38,000
After all, you're a new company.

242
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,000
I'm not fully clear on your capabilities yet.

243
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,760
Mr. Wang, we are newly established.

244
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,480
But we've also been involved in

245
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:45,960
many well-developed IP productions.

246
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:48,040
You don't need to worry about our expertise.

247
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:53,320
I've discussed this project with many teams.

248
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,720
If we're talking expertise,

249
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,400
you don't have the upper hand.

250
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:58,360
Mr. Wang.

251
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,800
Since you know we're a new company,

252
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:01,960
and still chose to meet with us,

253
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,000
and to hear our ideas,

254
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:04,440
that alone shows

255
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:06,520
you're open to working with us.

256
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,360
It comes down to

257
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,960
how well we show our sincerity.

258
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,560
Ms. Chu is very smart.

259
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,640
As for our company,

260
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,680
we don't just have original IPs.

261
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:15,840
We also choose

262
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,400
to invest in startups with profit sharing.

263
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,240
Are you aware of this plan?

264
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:21,720
Yes.

265
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,080
Mr. Wang, are you planning

266
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,560
to invest in our company?

267
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:30,200
It's not out of the question.

268
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:30,680
You see,

269
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,480
you're a startup team,

270
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:34,000
yet you're all industry veterans,

271
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:34,520
right?

272
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:37,240
You fit our criteria perfectly.

273
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,000
That's exactly what we're hoping for.

274
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:41,800
However,

275
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,360
like Ms. Chu said,

276
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,200
you still need to show me your sincerity.

277
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,800
It's not drinking again, is it?

278
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,880
If it's just drinks,

279
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,320
I could live with that.

280
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,400
Don't get me wrong.

281
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,760
That's not what we mean.

282
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:01,080
We're currently filming a new project.

283
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,760
I'd like Ms. Chu to come by

284
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,320
and do a two-day cameo.

285
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:04,880
This also

286
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:07,320
gives us a chance to see Ms. Chu's acting up close.

287
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:10,160
That's easy. Acting is my profession.

288
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,000
If my passion

289
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,040
can help my own people,

290
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,400
I'd be happy to.

291
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:16,120
It's settled.

292
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:17,800
Mr. Wang,

293
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,120
pleasure working with you.

294
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,320
Saying that now,

295
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,480
isn't it a bit early?

296
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,080
I'll do everything I can to make this happen.

297
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:27,760
Good.

298
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,800
I really admire your confidence.

299
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:32,080
Here we go.

300
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:32,760
Pleasure working together.

301
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:33,360
Sure.

302
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,520
It's been a long time since I was on set.

303
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,280
Not really.

304
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,400
Even though you stopped acting,

305
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:42,760
you still come to set all the time.

306
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,920
I mean as an actress.

307
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:46,560
Nervous?

308
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:47,520
A little.

309
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,480
It's okay, don't be nervous.

310
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:51,600
I've got you.

311
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:53,120
Yu, this next scene...

312
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:01,200
You've got to be kidding, he's still getting projects?

313
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,160
What a small world.

314
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:03,640
Let's go!

315
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:05,640
You don't want the IP anymore?

316
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,360
Who cares about the IP?

317
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,760
You can tell he's up to no good.

318
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:09,240
Besides,

319
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:09,880
Mr. Wang looks like

320
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,200
he's not that hard to talk to.

321
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:11,920
We can go ask him again.

322
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:12,200
Let's go.

323
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,800
Mr. Wang arranged for me to be here.

324
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:17,800
Do you think he didn't know who the director was?

325
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:20,600
Mr. Wang did it on purpose?

326
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:23,640
I want to prove it to them.

327
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:25,960
The past won't hold me back.

328
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:27,560
I'm moving forward.

329
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:28,080
You...

330
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,240
Relax, I know my limits.

331
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,400
Even if this place is a dump,

332
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:34,200
I won't let the stench

333
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,960
